tags.description: This structure is a fully enclosed single story connector between two buildings.
This is an open-air building with only two walls which contains storage lockers. It is used for the M-Air Drone Testing Facility.
This appears to be a mostly underground furnace room for the adjacent building.
This building probably contains electrical equipment for the wind tunnels.
This building contains an electrical switching substation and, at the east end, a maintenance shop.

tags.description: A cylindrical corrugated steel building with a painted mural on its dome. Contains wind tunnel equipment. Building is not open to the public.
The partially enclosed space below this roof contains storage lockers for drone test field users and a permanently attached table tennis game table.
Houses offices and studios for the Department of Dance in the the University of Michigan's School of Music, Theatre & Dance.
